Fix tournament room creation in APK builds

Root causes identified and fixed:

1. Global fetch vs expo/fetch mismatch
   All fetch calls in tournament.tsx used the global React Native `fetch`
   while the rest of the app used expo/fetch (undici-based). On Android APKs,
   the native fetch can behave differently for HTTPS/TLS connections to Railway.
   Fix: added `import { fetch } from "expo/fetch"` to tournament.tsx.

2. EXPO_PUBLIC_DOMAIN not baked into APK builds
   eas.json had no `env` section, so EXPO_PUBLIC_DOMAIN was undefined in APKs
   and relied entirely on the runtime fallback. Added it explicitly to all
   three build profiles (development/preview/production) to guarantee the
   correct Railway URL is always available.

3. No timeout — requests could hang indefinitely
   Added `safeFetch()` helper with 15s AbortController timeout and 2 retries
   with exponential backoff. Slow Railway cold-starts no longer surface
   as immediate errors.

4. socket.id used before socket connects
   `socket.id` is undefined until the socket.io handshake completes. In APK
   builds this can take longer. Fixed with `socket.id ?? ""` fallback in
   both create-and-join and confirm-join flows.

5. Better Arabic error messages
   "فشل إنشاء الغرفة" → "تعذر إنشاء الغرفة، حاول مرة أخرى"
   Network errors → "تعذر الاتصال بالخادم، تحقق من اتصالك وحاول مرة أخرى"

6. Null-safe array handling
   fetchTournaments now guards against null API responses with Array.isArray().

No multiplayer/game/socket logic was modified.
